# Documentation Discipline

## MUST

- Update documentation **before** changing scope, workflow, inputs, outputs, success metrics, or Series Memory behavior.
- Log unresolved decisions in `drift-log.md` using its entry template.
- Document proposed changes (what, why, documents affected) before implementing them.
- Keep `drift-log.md` current when validation reveals a needed spec change.

## MUST NOT

- Silently change product direction, workflow, audience, or outputs.
- Silently add scope or redesign flows in code.
- Fix spec conflicts only in implementation — update the authoritative doc first.
- Skip documentation because a change "seems small."

## Stop and update docs first if changes affect

- User workflow
- Required inputs or outputs
- Product philosophy or goals
- Scope boundaries or success metrics
- Series Memory behavior
- Domain ownership

## Order

Documentation changes first. Implementation changes second.
